section.def:
competent authority (主管當局), in relation to a place outside Hong Kong, means the authority
            responsible, under the law of that place, for the regulation of carriage of cargoes in
            that place;

paragraph.content:
must include information on the cargoes specified in section
                    4.2.2 of the IMSBC Code;
                    (L.N. 36 of 2019)

subsection.def:
moist cargo (含濕貨物) means a cargo that possesses a hazard due to moisture that may
                result in liquefaction or dynamic separation of the cargo if the cargo is shipped at
                a moisture content in excess of a certain limit;
